DTSTAMP:20260404T033044Z
UID:999272
DESCRIPTION:<p>Tony Award&reg\; winner Aaron Tveit (<em>Moulin Rouge!</em>
 )\, Emmy&reg\; Award nominee Lea Michele (<em>Funny Girl</em>\, <em>Glee</
 em>)\, and breakout powerhouse Nicholas Christopher (<em>Sweeney Todd</em>
 \, <em>Hamilton</em>) star on Broadway in <em>Chess</em> - the iconic musi
 cal where power and passion collide\, and the stakes couldn&rsquo\;t be hi
 gher.<br /><br />It&rsquo\;s America versus Russia at the World Chess Cham
 pionship\, where the espionage and romance are as complicated and exhilara
 ting as the game itself. For the two players and the woman torn between th
 em\, everything&mdash\;personal\, professional\, and political&mdash\;is a
 t risk&hellip\; and nobody&rsquo\;s rules are the same.<br /><br />With a 
 legendary score by ABBA&rsquo\;s Benny Andersson and Bj&ouml\;rn Ulvaeus\,
  lyrics by Emmy\, Grammy&reg\;\, Oscar&reg\; and Tony winner Tim Rice (<em
 >Evita</em>\, <em>Jesus Christ Superstar</em>)\, a new book by Emmy winner
  Danny Strong (<em>Dopesick</em>\, <em>The Butler</em>)\, and direction by
  Tony winner Michael Mayer (<em>Spring Awakening</em>\, <em>Hedwig and the
  Angry Inch</em>)\, <em>Chess</em> is the must-see Broadway event of the s
 eason.</p>
LOCATION:Imperial Theatre\, 249 West 45th Street\, New York NY 10036
END:VEVENT
